  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "A coset is a \"shifted copy\" of a [subgroup](./subgroup.md) within a larger [group](./group.md). Given a subgroup $H$ of a group $G$ and an element $g in G$, the left coset of $H$ by $g$ is $gH = {g cdot h : h in H}$ — you take every element of $H$ and multiply it on the left by $g$. The right coset is $Hg = {h cdot g : h in H}$ — you multiply on the right instead.",
  "name": "Coset",
